# Journally Landing Page

Standalone static landing page for Journally. It is intentionally separate from the Spring/Expo app and can be deployed directly to Netlify.

The contact form opens a pre-filled email to `service.journally@gmail.com`.

## Local Preview

From this folder:

```powershell
python -m http.server 4173 --bind 127.0.0.1
```

Open:

```text
http://127.0.0.1:4173/
```

## Netlify Deploy

### Manual deploy

1. Go to Netlify.
2. Open **Sites**.
3. Choose **Add new site**.
4. Choose **Deploy manually**.
5. Drag the `landing` folder into Netlify.

### CLI deploy

From this folder:

```powershell
netlify login
netlify deploy --dir . --prod
```

If `netlify` is not installed:

```powershell
npm install -g netlify-cli
```

## Git Deploy Note

The parent repository currently ignores `exportToHTML/`, so this folder will not be picked up by a Git-connected Netlify site unless the landing page is moved to a tracked folder or the parent `.gitignore` is adjusted.
